Welcome to the Interactive Physics engine!

WINDOWS: Go to "https://download-directory.github.io/" and copy the "INTERACTIVEPHYSICS" folder URL. Extract the files, open SETUP.EXE, and
follow all the instructions there to download. It will then ask you to insert your name, company, and serial number. Put the name and
company as whatever you would like and put "IP50T-00001-063019207" as the serial code. Wait some time for the installation to begin, and
then you can search "Interactive Physics" on the windows app searcher and open it up.

MAC: Regarding Apple computers' users, the SETUP.EXE does not function on the MacOS. You will need third-party softwares to run the 
SETUP.EXE like Parallels Desktop, or if you want to connect remotely to your Windows device from your Mac, Windows App. After you 
install and set up one of those, you can open the SETUP.EXE and proceed normally with the installation. You will have to download the
INTERACTIVEPHYSICS folder, extract it, run SETUP.EXE, follow the installation instructions, and do everything as in the Windows 
instructions.

IMPORTANT NOTE: In the installation process, it may give you a discreet hint to write "Demo" in where you are supposed to write the
serial number, however if you do this, you will enter the demo version, which functions exactly the same as the normal version except
you can't save your projects. If you just wanted to see the game overall, you should use the demo. However if you will consistently
use Interactive Phyisics, writing "IP50T-00001-063019207" on the serial number inserter is recommended.

THANK YOU FOR READING
